#: ../paint_box.rst:37
msgid "Lay out the drawing board, add Pen expansion function"
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:39
msgid ""
"First, we delete the previous sprite, and then add the Pencil sprite and "
"Block-X sprite to Scratch."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:41
msgid ""
"Upload **Eraser.svg, Red.png, Blue.png, Green.png, Yellow.png** and other"
" files in the Sprite list (You have downloaded from `raspad3.git "
"<https://github.com/sunfounder/raspad3.git>`_ before.), and finally set "
"the size of the Pencil sprite and Block-X sprite Change to 50."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:47
msgid "Then, we add the **Pen** extension function."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:54
msgid "Add drawing function to Pencil sprite"
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:56
msgid ""
"Click on the Pencil sprite. First, we need to make the Pencil sprite move"
" with the mouse. If the mouse button is pressed, we call the 「**pen "
"down**」 block in the Pen extension function, which can draw along the "
"track of the cursor. Otherwise, call the「**pen up**」 block to stop "
"drawing."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:62
msgid ""
"Click on the green flag and try to control the Pencil sprite with the "
"mouse to draw a smiley face. You will find that the image is not drawn "
"from the tip of the Pencil."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:65
msgid ""
"Since the cursor is not on the Pencil tip, the line drawn is drawn from "
"the middle of the Pencil sprite."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:67
msgid ""
"We click on the **Costumes**, select the entire Pencil sprite and move it"
" until the Pencil tip is aligned with the cross cursor."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:74
msgid "Let the Pencil sprite change the painting color."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:76
msgid ""
"How to achieve that when we click on the color option below the stage, "
"the Pencil sprite will switch the corresponding color?"
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:78
msgid ""
"First we write code for the Red sprite, when it is clicked, we broadcast "
"a new \"red\" message."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:84
msgid ""
"Then we return the code of the Pencil sprite, and when it receives the "
"\"red\" message, we change the color of the Pencil to red."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:90
msgid ""
"In the same way, we also write code for the Blue sprite, and when it is "
"clicked, we broadcast a new \"blue\" message."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:96
msgid ""
"Return the code of the Pencil sprite. When it receives the \"blue\" "
"message, we change the color of the Pencil to blue."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:98
msgid ""
"Before painting, we clear the scene on the stage and set the Pencil color"
" to red. Zoom in on the stage area and try your brush again."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:105
msgid "Add the function of clear drawing image."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:107
msgid ""
"Sometimes accidents happen when we draw, so we need to add a clear "
"function. First select the Block-X sprite, when it is clicked, we clear "
"all the screens."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:113
msgid ""
"Next, we set a new costume for the Pencil sprite, click the \"Costumes\" "
"tab, and then select the **Upload Costume** option from the icon on the "
"bottom left to upload the **Eraser.svg** file."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:115
msgid ""
"Modify the size of the Eraser garment appropriately, and then place it on"
" the upper right of the cursor."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:121
msgid ""
"We started programming the Eraser sprite, and when it was clicked, we "
"broadcast a new \"eraser\" message."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:127
msgid ""
"Then continue to add code for the Pencil sprite. When it receives the "
"\"eraser\" message, it will change to the Eraser costume,"
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:129
msgid ""
"so that when we click on the Eraser sprite, we can change the Pencil "
"sprite's costume to look like an Eraser sprite."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:131
msgid ""
"Then change the color to white that is consistent with the background "
"color of the stage, so as to achieve the function of partial removal."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:138
msgid "Toggle clothing and brush width tools."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:140
msgid ""
"When the costume of the Pencil sprite is switched to Eraser, we need to "
"switch the costume of the Pencil sprite to the Pencil-a costume by "
"clicking the red and blue on the drawing board, so when we receive the "
"\"red\" message and the \"blue\" message, We want to switch back to the "
"original Pencil-a costume."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:146
msgid ""
"In order to make our painting function more fun, we need to be able to "
"change the width of the Pencil at any time."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:148
msgid ""
"Create a new variable named \"width\", then right-click the \"width\" "
"variable on the stage, select slider, and then you will see a slider on "
"the stage that can change the value of the \"width\" variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:154
msgid "Use the value of the variable \"width\" as the size of the Pencil."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:161
msgid "Limit the painting range of the Pencil."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:163
msgid "Only when the Pencil enters the drawing area, can painting be allowed."
msgstr ""

#: ../paint_box.rst:169
msgid ""
"When the pen enters the toolbar, that is, when the y coordinate is less "
"than or equal to -120, we need to call the 「**pen up**」 function to stop "
"painting."
msgstr ""

